      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It sounds incredibly draining to feel like a constant burden to your daughter, especially when she is already carrying her own heavy load. Remember that family needs aren't zero-sum; by stepping back, you're giving her the space she needs to regroup and appreciate you when she does show up. Giving yourself permission to ask for help is an act of love that actually protects the relationship from the stress you're both feeling.",
